# infra/optimism-mainnet/.env — Ophis Optimism mainnet secrets.
# COPY this file to .env, fill in the secrets, NEVER COMMIT the populated form.
# .gitignore already excludes infra/optimism-mainnet/.env.
#
# After copying, chmod 600 .env — render-configs.sh enforces this on every
# deploy but the initial copy is on the operator. This keeps the
# OKX credentials owner-only at the filesystem layer.
#
# NOTE (2026-05-18, Tier 1 PK isolation): the driver-submitter PK is no
# longer stored in the macOS Keychain or this .env file. It lives at
# /Users/ophis-driver/.config/submitter.key (0600, owned by ophis-driver
# user). render-configs.sh reads it via sudo at deploy time.
#
# NOTE (2026-05-19, Phase 4 audit M H3 honesty fix): OKX, CoinGecko, and
# Postgres credentials live HERE in this .env at chmod 600. The earlier
# comment claimed OKX creds live in Keychain — that was aspirational,
# never implemented. .env at chmod 600 is the actually-working path.
# Threat model: any process running as scep can read .env. Tier 1.5
# (RAM-disk render) or Tier 2 (per-secret manager) closes this. Until
# then, keep .env on FileVault-encrypted disk + Mac mini's physical
# security as the only barriers.

# ── Database ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Pick a strong random password (32+ chars). Different from testnet (which
# uses '123' for convenience). Generate via:
#   openssl rand -base64 32
POSTGRES_USER=ophis
POSTGRES_PASSWORD=
POSTGRES_DB=ophis
DB_WRITE_URL=postgresql://ophis:${POSTGRES_PASSWORD}@db:5432/ophis
DB_READ_URL=postgresql://ophis:${POSTGRES_PASSWORD}@db:5432/ophis

# ── Chain RPC ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# publicnode.com (free, no API key, eth_createAccessList works). Fallback to
# https://op-pokt.nodies.app by editing this if publicnode degrades.
OP_MAINNET_RPC=https://optimism-rpc.publicnode.com

# ── Driver-submitter private key ──────────────────────────────────────────
# Corresponds to on-chain address 0x00f98b5776eb0f6a8c0c925ddF51f9Ade8a1502F,
# which was allowlisted in deploy-mainnet-all.sh Step 3 (addSolver). This EOA
# signs every settlement transaction. Treat like a hot-wallet key — keep
# balance bounded (~0.02 OP ETH, top up as needed) to cap blast radius.
#
# DEPRECATED post-Tier-1 PK isolation (2026-05-18). The PK now lives at
# /Users/ophis-driver/.config/submitter.key and is read by render-configs.sh
# directly. Leave this var empty in production .env.
OPHIS_DRIVER_SUBMITTER_KEY=

# ── OKX aggregator solver credentials ─────────────────────────────────────
# All 4 fields are required by apps/backend/crates/solvers OKX module.
# Create at https://web3.okx.com/build → API keys → New key with scopes:
# Trade + Read on the OnchainOS DEX product. Copy each field below.
#
# IMPORTANT: do NOT add a payment method on the OKX dashboard. The API
# caps at the $100 Basic + $50 Premium monthly free quota and stops
# responding (rather than billing) once exceeded. Caps financial risk
# at $0/mo.
#
# Rotation procedure if leaked: OKX dashboard → revoke old key → create
# new with same scopes → update lines below → run render-configs.sh →
# `docker compose restart okx-solver`. Verify with a sample quote via
# orderbook /api/v1/quote.
OKX_PROJECT_ID=
OKX_API_KEY=
OKX_SECRET_KEY=
OKX_PASSPHRASE=

# ── CoinGecko (native-price oracle for autopilot + orderbook) ─────────────
# Required by docker-compose.yml — autopilot and orderbook fail-fast at
# startup if unset. Get a free key at
# https://www.coingecko.com/en/api/pricing — the free Demo tier allows
# 30 calls/min, 10K calls/month, enough for OP-only operation.
COINGECKO_API_KEY=
